                            <comment id="12737204" author="mikedd" created="Thu, 30 Jul 2009 19:04:51 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Currently trunk uses the default derby.locks.waitTimeout (60) and a derby.locks.deadlockTimeout of 5. I suspect that these can be tuned for the developer&apos;s hardware and provide quicker test execution. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;anecdotal evidence&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
setting waitTimeout = 10 saved me 5 - 10 minutes on a build last night. &lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;/anecdotal evidence&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The properties can be specified on the command line : &lt;br/&gt;
$ mvn -Dderby.locks.deadlockTimeout=10 -Dderby.locks.waitTimeout=15 clean test&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;or in settings.xml : &lt;br/&gt;
       &amp;lt;profile&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
            &amp;lt;id&amp;gt;derby-locking&amp;lt;/id&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
            &amp;lt;properties&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
                &amp;lt;derby.locks.deadlockTimeout&amp;gt;3&amp;lt;/derby.locks.deadlockTimeout&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
                &amp;lt;derby.locks.waitTimeout&amp;gt;5&amp;lt;/derby.locks.waitTimeout&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
            &amp;lt;/properties&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
        &amp;lt;/profile&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; The profile (as shown) needs to be activated on the command line  : &lt;br/&gt;
 $ mvn -Pderby-locking clean test&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12737232" author="mikedd" created="Thu, 30 Jul 2009 19:58:39 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;The values in the profile might not work well on trunk (I haven&apos;t tried) - they should be good for earlier releases (1.0.x).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The earlier releases do not include an extensive lock manager test suite. The lock manager test suite is sensitive to these settings and has been known to cause problems with deadlockTimeout=5, waitTimeout=6. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Some experimentation (without local changes) is advised before changing them in your environment (YMMV). &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
